&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Executive Administrator to serve as the primary executive support to our CEO and assist other members of Clever&#39;s Executive Leadership Team as needed. This is a high-impact, highly trusted role in a primarily remote environment, with occasional travel for key in-person meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Clever continues to grow and evolve, this person will help our CEO and leadership team stay organized, aligned, and prepared through moments of change. You&#39;ll bring structure to shifting priorities, help make communication smoother across stakeholders, and create the operational clarity leaders need to move work forward thoughtfully.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be someone who can read the room, even virtually; anticipate what the CEO and other leaders need; and keep priorities, calendars, travel, and logistics moving smoothly. You&#39;ll help reduce administrative friction, create clarity, and make sure our leaders are prepared for the moments that matter most.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a great fit for someone who is resourceful, detail-oriented, thrives in a fast-moving, collaborative environment, and is confident navigating competing priorities. If you enjoy solving problems before they become problems, building trust across multiple stakeholders, and helping a mission-driven organization run more effectively, we&#39;d love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You’ll Make an Impact:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work proactively to help the CEO operate at optimal capacity.&lt;/strong&gt; As primary support to our CEO, you&#39;ll manage complex calendars, resolve scheduling conflicts, coordinate travel, and clear administrative noise, while also extending support to other executives as capacity allows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide excellent remote-first executive support. &lt;/strong&gt;Most of your work will be done virtually, so you&#39;ll need to be proactive, responsive, and thoughtful in how you support leaders from afar. You&#39;ll know when to move quickly, when to ask the right questions, and when to make a judgment call.&lt;/li&gt;
