&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own bottom-of-funnel operations: pipeline review, renewal forecasting, NRR/GRR tracking, and contraction analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build data-driven recommendations end-to-end — from the initial model to the leadership presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive ARR dashboard automation and reduce reliance on manual data reconciliation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own cross-sell pipeline visibility and white space analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Process &amp;amp; systems&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean up legacy processes while continuing to build — this is the most important challenge for this hire in year one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and improve account segmentation, territory modeling, and quota/capacity planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Salesforce and BI teams (Sigma) to strengthen reporting infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to lead lifecycle management, marketing-to-sales handoff, and funnel optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cross-functional leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a thought partner to Sales, CS, and Marketing leaders — elevating the credibility and strategic footprint of the RevOps function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead change management across teams; frame process improvements as optimization, not criticism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business questions into analytical frameworks — start with “what are we trying to answer?” before building anything&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
